# Optional: full API origin when not using Vite dev proxy (e.g. production build served separately).
# Leave unset in dev so requests go to same origin /api (Vite proxies to the backend — avoids CORS).
# If you set http://localhost:8080 here, the browser calls the API directly; the backend must allow your dev origin (see app.cors.allowed-origin-patterns in backend application.yml).
# VITE_API_BASE_URL=http://localhost:8080

# Optional: enables Google sign-in button in the login page.
# Must match the same OAuth Web Client ID configured in backend GOOGLE_CLIENT_ID.
# VITE_GOOGLE_CLIENT_ID=your-google-web-client-id.apps.googleusercontent.com

# --- DevTools checklist (when debugging 403 / CORS) ---
# 1. Request URL: same-origin dev should be http://localhost:<vite-port>/api/... — not http://localhost:8080 unless VITE_API_BASE_URL is set.
# 2. Request headers: POST/PATCH/DELETE should include Authorization: Basic ... (from session after login).
# 3. Account: POST /api/v1/resources requires ROLE_ADMIN — use an administrator account (see backend README for bootstrap admin env vars).

# --- Prefer proxy in local dev (recommended) ---
# - Remove or comment out VITE_API_BASE_URL in .env (or do not define it), then restart the Vite dev server so /api is same-origin and proxied to Spring.

# --- CORS troubleshooting (browser ↔ API on different origins) ---
# - In local dev, leave VITE_API_BASE_URL unset so the app uses /api on the Vite origin; the proxy forwards to Spring and the browser does not need CORS.
# - If you set VITE_API_BASE_URL to the API host (e.g. http://localhost:8080), your page origin (e.g. http://localhost:5174) must be allowed by the backend CORS list; add patterns in application.yml or APP_CORS_ALLOWED_ORIGIN_PATTERNS_* env vars.
# - After changing backend CORS settings, restart the Spring Boot app.
# - Common mistakes: wrong port, using a LAN IP for the page but only localhost allowed, or http vs https mismatch.
